			<tr>
                <td bgcolor="#5f88fe"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#ffffff"><strong>W
                e d n e s d a y</strong></font></td>
                <td align="right" bgcolor="#5f88fe"><font
                size="2" face="Arial" color="#ffffff"><strong>O/N Galilee</strong></font></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td colspan="2"><font size="2" face="Arial">Drive north via Netania to Caesarea,
				 once the Roman capital of the Holyland. See the excavations of the Roman statues,
				 the aqueduct and the amphitheater, which was restored to its former glory as a concert venue.
				 Proceed to Megiddo to see the excavations of King Solomon's stables and 20 layers of civilization.
				 Drive north via Haifa and Mount Carmel for a panoramic view of the city and the bay.
				 Visit the Persian Garden of the Bahai Shrine. Proceed to Tzippori (Sepphoris) to see the
				 magnificent mosaic floors, Crusader castle and church.  Continue to Tiberias for overnight.
				</font></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#5f88fe"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#ffffff"><strong>T
                h u r s d a y</strong></font></td>
                <td align="right" bgcolor="#5f88fe"><font
                size="2" face="Arial" color="#ffffff"><strong>O/N Galilee</strong></font></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td colspan="2"><font size="2" face="Arial">Embark on a short boat trip on the Sea of Galilee.
				 On to Capernaum, ancient synagogue of the Second Temple period and the house of St. Peter.
				 Continue to Tabgha, where the miracle of the multiplication of the Loaves and the Fishes was performed.
				 Drive to the summit of the Mt. of Beatitudes, site of the Sermon on the Mount.
				 Proceed north to Caesarea Philippi (Banias) and the sources of the Jordan River. 
				 Return to Tiberias for overnight.
				</font></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#5f88fe"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#ffffff"><strong>F
                r i d a y</strong></font></td>
                <td align="right" bgcolor="#5f88fe"><font
                size="2" face="Arial" color="#ffffff"><strong>O/N Jerusalem</strong></font></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td colspan="2"><font size="2" face="Arial">En route to Nazareth via Cana, the site of the first miracle.
				 Arrive Nazareth and visit the Basilica of Annunciation, Mary's Well  and St. Joseph's Carpentry shop.
				 Continue to Yardenit, the Baptismal site.   Proceed to Beit Shean. Visit the excavations of the former
				 Roman city. Drive through the Jordan Valley, via Jericho, the oldest city in the world,
				 to Jerusalem for overnight.
				</font></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#5f88fe"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#ffffff"><strong>S
                a t u r d a y</strong></font></td>
                <td align="right" bgcolor="#5f88fe"><font
                size="2" face="Arial" color="#ffffff"><strong>O/N Jerusalem</strong></font></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td colspan="2"><font size="2" face="Arial">Start the day with a visit to Mt. of Olives 
				 for a panoramic view of Jerusalem. Continue to the Garden of Gethsemane and visit the 
				 Basilica of the Agony. Tour the Old City of Jerusalem, the Western Wall,
				 the Temple Mount and the Dome of the Rock (entrance to the Mosques not included).
				 Walk along the Via Dolorosa and visit the Church of the Holy Sepulchre. On to Mt. Zion 
				 to see David's Tomb, the room of the Last Supper and the Dormition Abbey.
				 Visit the Cardo and the bazaar before returning to your hotel.
				</font></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#5f88fe"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#ffffff"><strong>S
                u n d a y</strong></font></td>
                <td align="right" bgcolor="#5f88fe"><font
                size="2" face="Arial" color="#ffffff"><strong>O/N Jerusalem</strong></font></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td colspan="2"><font size="2" face="Arial">Visit the Israel Museum's Shrine of the Book,
				 where the Dead Sea Scrolls are displayed. Continue to Yad Vashem, the memorial to the six
				 million Jewish victims of the Holocaust. On to the model of Jerusalem during the Second Temple period.
				 The last stop of the day is in Bethlehem to visit the Church of the Nativity and Manger Square.
				 Return to Jerusalem for overnight.
				</font></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td bgcolor="5f88fe"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#ffffff"><strong>M
                o n d a y</strong></font></td>
                <td align="right" bgcolor="#5f88fe"><font
                size="2" face="Arial" color="#ffffff"><strong>O/N Jerusalem</strong></font></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td colspan="2"><font size="2" face="Arial">Leave Jerusalem and drive via Ma'ale Adumim and 
				 the Good Samaritan Inn. Descend through the Judean Desert to the salty shores of the Dead Sea,
				 the world's lowest point (390 m. below sea level). Ascend by cable car to the spectacular Zealot
				 fortress of Massada. Time for a quick dip in the Dead Sea (weather permitting).  Continue to Qumran,
				 to visit the site where the Dead Sea Scrolls were found.  Return to Jerusalem, stopping at a diamond
				 center for a visit, before arriving at  your hotel. 
				</font></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#5f88fe"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#ffffff"><strong>T
                u e s d a y</strong></font></td>
                <td align="right" bgcolor="#5f88fe" color="#ffffff">&nbsp;</td>
            </tr>
